<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SALIDA; 
</P>
<P>
SLAYINGS LINKED TO WHITE GROUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four suspects arrested in the murders of four people found in a dilapidated 
duplex containing drug paraphernalia are members of a white supremacist group, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
"The common thread we're finding is they all belonged to what appears to be a 
self-proclaimed white supremacist-type group," Stanislaus County Sheriff's Lt. 
Richard Breshears said. "There doesn't appear to be any racial overtones in 
this (the four victims were white). The motive is really up in the air a 
little." Some of the victims reportedly knew the suspects and apparently were 
specific targets in the slayings, Breshears said. The others might have been 
"at the wrong place at the wrong time," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
