<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: VENTURA; 
</P>
<P>
WOMAN ARRESTED IN DEATH OF ROOMMATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 24-year-old Ventura woman has been arrested on suspicion of voluntary 
manslaughter in the death of her 27-year-old roommate, who allegedly was pushed 
down a flight of stairs. 
</P>
<P>
Valerie Jean Rhodehamel, 24, was being held in lieu of $10,000 bail at the Main 
Jail in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura Police Sgt. Roger Nustad said Rhodehamel and the victim, Mary Elizabeth 
Feeney, had been feuding all day Sunday over Feeney's former boyfriend, who was 
visiting their apartment at 239 Ramona St. 
</P>
<P>
About 9:45 p.m., Rhodehamel tried to prevent Feeney from going downstairs to 
join the man and four other friends, Nustad said. He said a witness told police 
that Rhodehamel apparently changed her mind and pushed Feeney. 
</P>
<P>
Feeney fell about nine feet down the stairs, striking her head and cracking her 
skull, Nustad said. She was taken to the Ventura County Medical Center, where 
she died at 8:15 p.m. Monday said a spokeswoman for the Ventura County 
coroner's office. CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
