<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WOMAN KILLED AS CAR PLUNGES OFF OCEAN CLIFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman was killed Wednesday when her station wagon plunged off a road and 
crashed at the bottom of a 300-foot ocean cliff in Palos Verdes Estates, police 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
The woman, identified as Martha Howard, 55, was thrown from the car. 
</P>
<P>
A passerby spotted Howard's vehicle at the bottom of the cliff in the 1300 
block of Palos Verdes Drive West in the Bluff Cove area about 3 p.m. and 
flagged down police. 
</P>
<P>
Howard's body was found nearby. 
</P>
<P>
Police were investigating whether the death was a suicide. 
</P>
