<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: PORT HUENEME; 
</P>
<P>
SUSPECT IN 20 HOME BURGLARIES ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Port Hueneme police on Wednesday arrested a 21-year-old man suspected of 
burglarizing as many as 20 houses in the city's south area over the past two 
weeks, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
John Charles Jacobson of Port Hueneme was being held on six counts of burglary 
after he was arrested while trying to crawl out the back window of his house in 
the 100 block of East C Street, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Detective Dale Harbin, who investigates burglary cases for the Port Hueneme 
Police Department, recognized Jacobson from a description given by a woman who 
saw the suspect burglarizing her house, Police Sgt. Dennis Fitzgerald said. 
</P>
<P>
Jacobson's fingerprints matched those found in six houses that had been 
burglarized of videocassette recorders, jewelry and money, Fitzgerald said. 
</P>
<P>
Police obtained a warrant and searched Jacobson's house but did not find any of 
the stolen goods, Fitzgerald said. They believe Jacobson sold the goods 
immediately after stealing them, Fitzgerald said. CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
