<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MIDWAY BAPTIST WINS, REACHES 1-A SEMIFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Steve Smith struck out seven in four innings to raise his season total to 116 
in 68 innings as Midway Baptist beat La Jolla Country Day, 8-5, in the 
quarterfinals of the San Diego Section 1-A baseball playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
Midway Baptist (20-3), seeded No. 1, twice came through with big hits -- Jeff 
Moore drove in two runs with a two-out single in the first, and Chris Mulkey 
knocked in two runs with a two-out triple in the third. 
</P>
<P>
David Eichenlaub hit an inside-the-park home run for Midway Baptist in the 
fifth. 
</P>
<P>
In the sixth, La Jolla Country Day (9-15-1) loaded the bases for Damian 
Campbell, who hit a shot into right center on which right fielder Craig Foster 
made an airborne diving catch to keep the Torres from tying. 
</P>
<P>
In other 1-A quarterfinals: 
</P>
<P>
Holtville 5, Bishop's 1 -- Holtville advances to the Friday's semifinals, in 
which it will play Midway Baptist at Mar Vista at 3:30 p.m. Bishop's finished 
at 10-9-1. 
</P>
<P>
Julian 12, Borrego Springs 5 -- John Hockin, who has batted only three times in 
Julian's past eight games, pinch hit in the fifth inning with two out, a man on 
and Julian (15-8) up by one. He came through with a home run for what turned 
out to be the game-winning hit. 
</P>
<P>
Borrego Springs finished 8-10-1. 
</P>
<P>
Imperial 10, Mountain Empire 6 -- Imperial (12-6-3), seeded No. 3, goes on to 
play Julian, the No. 2 seed, in the semifinals at Ramona High on Friday. 
Mountain Empire finished at 12-8-1. 
</P>
<P>
Boys' Tennis 
</P>
<P>
3-A Semifinals 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel 10, Mira Mesa 8 -- Mt. Carmel's No. 2 singles player, George Lobb, 
provided the margin of victory with two close victories. He first won a 7-3 
tiebreaker after ending a set with Ryan Connors at 6-6. Later he fell behind Ed 
Hendrickson, 4-3, before coming back for a 7-5 victory. 
</P>
<P>
Poway 13, Hilltop 5 -- Poway's doubles teams -- Jeff Marshall-Brian Dulac, Kofi 
Dartey-Tom Giesen and Blake Helander-David Anet -- didn't lose a set, and in 
singles, Poway's Rick Spooner won two of three sets. Poway, seeded first, goes 
against No. 2 Mt. Carmel today in the finals at Morley Field (3 p.m.). 
</P>
<P>
2-A Semifinals 
</P>
<P>
La Jolla 16, USDHS 2 -- La Jolla, seeded first, had little trouble advancing to 
today's finals. No. 2 and 3 singles players Tim Kreysing and Jim Brown swept, 
as did the doubles teams of James Conda-Jon Elsberry and Trevor Hess-Kenny 
Park. 
</P>
<P>
St. Augustine 13, San Pasqual 5 -- St. Augustine's singles players, including 
No. 1 Ignacio Martinez, the defending individual section champion, and German 
Aragon swept in the upset of the second-seeded team. St. Augustine, seeded 
third, meets La Jolla in today's finals at Morley Field (1 p.m.) 
</P>
<P>
Badminton 
</P>
<P>
No. 1 Chris Hansen of University City advanced to the section boys' singles 
final by defeating Tho Thai of Crawford, 15-6, 15-5, at Serra. 
</P>
<P>
Hansen will play Somsack Monsavath of San Diego for the title at 2 p.m. today 
at Serra. Monsavath defeated Steve Hashimoto of Serra, 5-3, 0-5, 15-10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
