<P>
Photo, Festive Fund-Raiser: It was Mardi Gras in Westwood on Saturday with the 
carnival atmosphere of New Orleans transferred to the UCLA campus. UCLA theater 
arts major, Neal Racioppo, 21, made the rounds as a clown, while children spun 
around in the spinning tunnel ride. Still others opted to go up and around on 
the Ferris wheel. In another area, Carlos Reynosa, 24, of the band Blue Sofa 
sang to a crowd gathered at the UCLA Athletic Field. The event is a traditional 
fund-raiser held by the university to raise money for charities. LISA ROMEREIN 
/ Los Angeles Times 
