<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: BEVERLY HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
ARTIST OF YEAR ANNOUNCED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
David Hockney has been named 1990 Artist of the Year by the University Women of 
the University of Judaism. 
</P>
<P>
Hockney, whose paintings, photo collages and other works often make use of the 
Southern California landscape, will be presented with the group's Burning Bush 
Award at its 24th annual Author/Artist Luncheon on June 7 at the Beverly Hilton 
Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
The luncheon is the spring fund-raiser for the university support group. The 
Burning Bush Award is given annually to a person who has made an enduring 
contribution to society. Past recipients include architect Frank Gehry, writer 
Isaac Bashevis Singer, actress Helen Hayes and director Stanley Kramer. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets for the luncheon are $65. For further information, call 476-9777, Ext. 
283. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
