<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: $56-MILLION BUDGET UNVEILED FOR COLLEGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Glendale College officials Monday unveiled a draft $56-million balanced budget 
for 1990-91, up 14% from the present year. 
</P>
<P>
Sam Black, college director of accounting, told the Board of Trustees that the 
increase consisted mainly of about $1 million to pay a 6.2% salary hike and a 
$6-million increase in capital expenditures for campus renovation. 
</P>
<P>
Campus construction was projected at $16.3 million, including $3.9 million for 
a permanent adult community training facility, $1.9 million to renovate the 
administration building, $3 million to reconfigure the auditorium, $3.2 million 
to upgrade the technical education buildings and $1.4 million to build an 
emergency access road across campus. 
</P>
<P>
The board is scheduled to adopt the preliminary budget June 18 and will hold a 
public hearing before adopting the final budget Aug. 27. 
</P>
