<HEADLINE>
<P>
PARAMOUNT ADVANCES TO QUARTERFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paramount High, with a 7-3 victory over Magnolia on Tuesday, has advanced to 
the CIF Southern Section baseball 4-A quarterfinals for the first time in six 
years. 
</P>
<P>
The Pirates (16-4) will play Upland at home Friday afternoon at 3:30. 
</P>
<P>
Other winning area teams in second-round games Tuesday were: 
</P>
<P>
* La Serna, which beat Bellflower, 6-1, in Division 3-A behind the pitching of 
Bryan Dunagan. The Lancers (25-5) will play host to Saugus on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
* Valley Christian, which defeated Temecula Valley, 4-1, in 2-A. Catcher Royal 
Lord broke a 1-1 tie with a two-run double for the 19-3 Crusaders, who will be 
at El Segundo on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
* St. Anthony, which beat Whittier Christian, 15-5, in 2-A. The Saints (14-9) 
play Friday at Santa Ynez. 
</P>
<P>
* Leffingwell Christian, which upset second-seeded Highland Hall, 7-7, in Small 
Schools. The Lions (12-7) will be at Woodcrest Christian on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
In softball, St. Joseph of Lakewood (14-10) will play host to Fountain Valley 
(21-6) in a 5-A quarterfinal game at 3 p.m. today. 
</P>
<P>
In 3-A second-round games Tuesday, Bellflower (23-6) defeated South Torrance, 
3-0; La Mirada (23-6) routed Ontario, 11-0, and Mayfair (18-10) edged Tustin, 
1-0. 
</P>
<P>
In 2-A, Santa Fe (23-1) advanced with a 2-0 victory over Cajon. 
</P>
