<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: RALLY MARKS ANNIVERSARY OF END OF SIX-DAY 
WAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City officials and supporters of Israel attended a rally in front of City Hall 
in downtown Los Angeles Wednesday to mark the 23rd anniversary of the end of 
The Six-Day War that united Israel's capital, Jerusalem. 
</P>
<P>
Mayor Tom Bradley's office proclaimed May 23 "Jerusalem Day," corresponding to 
the Hebrew calendar date on which the war between Israel and Jordan for control 
of the city ended. 
</P>
<P>
Elementary school students from Temple Beth Am's Pressman Academy in West Los 
Angeles sang popular Israeli songs as several city officials listened. 
</P>
<P>
The rally was sponsored by the Jewish Federation Council of Los Angeles, which 
organizes a social service exchange program between Los Angeles and Jerusalem. 
Israeli Consulate General in Los Angeles Ran Ronen read from a letter prepared 
for the ceremony by the mayor of Jerusalem, Teddy Kolleck, urging better 
understanding and mutual respect between various ethnic groups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
