<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIELD HOCKEY EVENT SLATED AT MOORPARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 19th California Cup field hockey tournament will be held at Moorpark 
College on Saturday through Monday. 
</P>
<P>
With 67 teams and more than 700 players, this year's field is the Cup's 
largest. Competition will be held in a variety of divisions based on sex and 
age. 
</P>
<P>
Teams from West Germany, India, Mexico, Taiwan and other countries will 
participate as well as about 20 teams from Ventura County. Some foreign teams 
reportedly will include Olympians. 
</P>
<P>
Competition begins each day at 7:30 a.m. The championship games in each 
division of the round-robin tournaments will be played Monday. 
</P>
