<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION SOFTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ST. MARGARET'S POUNDS ROSAMOND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harper Maycock and Wendy Tacquard each hit two home runs to lead visiting St. 
Margaret's High School to a 20-11 victory over host Rosamond in Southern 
Section Small Schools Division second-round softball game Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Colette McClaughlin (11-4) struck out 13 and also got offensive help from Sam 
Ruh, who hit a two-run triple, and Calle Anderson, who had two hits and scored 
four runs for St. Margaret's (11-5). 
</P>
