<TEXT>
<P>
The Soviet Union presents huge opportunities for foreign insurers if it 
succeeds in reforming its economy, the chairman of the Lloyd's of London 
insurance market said today. 
</P>
<P>
"We have to be optimistic and take the view that they're going to become part 
of the modern world in which case there has to be a colossal opportunity," 
Murray Lawrence told a wire service. 
</P>
<P>
Lawrence is heading a Lloyd's team in Moscow for talks with Soviet state 
insurance companies to see what role the world's largest insurance market could 
play in the Soviet Union. 
</P>
