<TEXT>
<P>
Look out, Washington -- Warren Beatty is bringing his big new picture "Dick 
Tracy" to town, and his co-star and sometime companion Madonna may also be here 
for the premiere. 
</P>
<P>
No one will confirm that the rock superstar is coming, but Madonna will be at 
Capital Centre in Landover, Md., the same June weekend performing in her 
"Blonde Ambition" concert tour. 
</P>
<P>
Walt Disney Co. says the film's "world" premiere will be at Disney World on 
June 14, but one could argue that the true premiere opening will be at the 
Uptown Theater on June 10, with a party afterward at the National Building 
Museum. 
</P>
<P>
Beatty is bringing the premiere to Washington -- where he grew up -- to benefit 
Johns Hopkins University School of Medicine's hematology research. 
