<P>
DUNCKEL'S 2 HOME RUNS LEAD TO SAN DIEGO STATE WIN AT REGIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STANFORD 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leadoff batter Bill Dunckel, who hit only four home runs during the regular 
season, homered in his first two at-bats today to power San Diego State to an 
18-6 victory over Middle Tennessee State in the opening game of the NCAA West I 
Regional tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Dunckel, who also doubled and singled, drove in six runs as Western Athletic 
Conference champion San Diego State, seeded third in the regional, improved its 
record to 47-20. 
</P>
<P>
Starter Kurt Archer (8-2) pitched 8 1/3 innings for the Aztecs, who advance to 
a second-round game Friday against either Southern Illinois or Cal State 
Fresno. 
</P>
<P>
Southern Illinois and Cal State Fresno were scheduled to play the second game 
in the tournament this afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
Fourth-seeded Middle Tennessee State, the Ohio Valley Conference champion, 
slipped to 42-14. 
</P>
<P>
After Middle Tennessee State had scored two runs in the top of the first, 
Dunckel hit the first pitch from MTSU starter Chris Crabtree (10-2) over the 
left-field fence. San Diego State went on to take a 3-2 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Dunckel hit his second homer, a three-run shot, as San Diego scored four runs 
in the second. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego scored three runs in the sixth, three in the seventh and five in the 
eighth, as the Aztecs totaled 17 hits off four MTSU pitchers and took advantage 
of nine walks and five errors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
